docBody.p:
I recd the Gorilla Treatise;
Richard Owen, Memoir on the Gorilla (1865).
 and have even read it,—with more understanding of it than might have been expected from my deficiency of anatomical Latin; and with a great deal more of interest than the horrible & indeed to me entirely detestable brutes ever awakened in me before. Complete knowledge is welcome on all subjects, even on ‘Gorillas’ and the Devil!—

ps.p:
Jamie is come (12.30 p.m.) tho I have not yet seen him,—till he finish dining. I meanwhile have finished Lady A (brief as possible, if kindly enough); & must go into that. Walking ought to be ahead; dinner at 4: the rain it raineth;
See Twelfth Night 5.1.
 but I have Mackh, a pair (one pair) of shoes that will turn mud. God send me good news on Tuesday morning; that is at prest the sum of my desires.

docBody.p:
But I must study brevity—the soul of wit;
Cf. Hamlet 2:2.
 for the cost of phisicalpain at which I write is something you can hardly conceive!

ps.p:
Must I return both the Photos? I have marked (in dim blue) my judgt. Can you send me some more of the former most approved Photo, also perhaps of this prest.— Item I forgot altogether my blacklead Bramah pencil;
A “propelling pencil,” patented in 1822 by Sampson Mordan (1790–1843 [not 1881 as previously noted at 39:178]), previously an apprentice of Joseph Bramah (1749–1814;  ODNB ). A combination Mordan pencil and Bramah pen was also available.
 and often want it more orless.—T.C.

“silence” Froude is probably quite right to dislike the Bust;
Woolner’s bust of TC; see JWC to TC, 6 June.
 I myself am no judge; but cannot say I have the least real liking for it. Mum!

docBody.p:
It is possible you may have other company just now; possible you may not be at Alderley at all! What I can do, is to write this Letter under the rose;
That is, sub rosa, privately.
 to give you Jane’s Address (“Holm Hill, Thornhill, Dumfriesshire”); and to say that if, on or before Saturday morning, “Sabbath desecratn and no Post after 
that” next, you asked her, I think she wd come;
Lady Stanley replied, 19 July: “You are a real friend I have written to your wife to beg of her to rest with us.”
 & that if you don’t write at all, this too will be an answer (and nobody but yr Ladyship & I the wiser!) abundtly suffict.

Ah! and, when I return “forty years” hence, let me find that dear we[e] well better kept! A modest stone trough holding its crystal water together, and a weeping willow to mark the spot! (Expenses defrayed by a Church-collection; the Sermon preached by—what’s your Xian name? Ben—Morrison—from the touching text— “Lo! all ye that thirst”!
Cf. Isaiah 55:1.
 )

Here we are Dear, all safe,—only I have given you a wrong Address;
TC referred to Hanover St. (where the Misses Orrocks lived previously) in TC to JWC, 8 [7] Aug.
 the real Address is

